<section_header_level_1><loc_89><loc_101><loc_254><loc_109>A. Readitlon  of Overtiae Servlces</section_header_level_1>
<ordered_list><list_item><loc_91><loc_115><loc_443><loc_131>The following steps shall be followed prior to the rendition of overtime sen,lces:</list_item>
</ordered_list>
<section_header_level_1><loc_105><loc_140><loc_304><loc_147>a. Requeat to Reader Overtime Senrices</section_header_level_1>
<ordered_list><list_item><loc_125><loc_154><loc_444><loc_200>Teachers  who intend to render overtime  services  shall accomplish and sub'nit the Request  for  Autlaity to Render Work Begond  Regular Hours, Weekends and Holidays (Annex  A), clearly indicating the date and time of the expected  overtime  work, the specific purpose or task to be completed,  and a justification explaining the necessit5r  of such services.</list_item>
<list_item><loc_125><loc_208><loc_444><loc_231>In the same manner, school heads or the authorized  approving authority may initiate requests  for teachers to render overtime services  based on operational needs.</list_item>
</ordered_list>
<section_header_level_1><loc_104><loc_238><loc_444><loc_247>b. Apptowal by the School Head or the authorized  approving authority</section_header_level_1>
<ordered_list><list_item><loc_125><loc_253><loc_445><loc_285>The School Head or the authorized  approving authority  shall review and evaluate  all requests  whether initiated by teachers or tJre administration,  based on the urgency  and relevance  of the task. If deemed appropriate,  approval shall be granted.</list_item>
<list_item><loc_125><loc_293><loc_444><loc_316>The School Head or the authorized  approving authority  reserves the right to approve or disapprove  the request depending on the nature and urgency of t1le work involved.</list_item>
<list_item><loc_125><loc_323><loc_444><loc_339>iii.The approved Annex A shall serve as tl:e Authority to Render Overtime  Services.</list_item>
</ordered_list>
